      <h2 id="words">Word &amp; Phrase Bank</h2>
      <div class="sub-section" id="word-and-phrase"><p class='section-intro'>These are words and phrases you may use to identify parts of our business and tools with any external audience.</p>
      <div class="words">
          <h3>[Ahalogy] Code Snippet</h3><p>The Ahalogy Code Snippet is a key aspect of being in the Content Network. It will track all of the performance data for the pins you publish through our tools. Additionally, it produces the Engagement when a reader clicks through to your site form Pinterest, prompting them to follow your profile.</p>
   
          <h3>[Ahalogy] Content Network</h3><p>The Ahalogy Content Network is a place to share and discover meaningful, proven content. You're able to filter by category to find specific content types that pique your personal interest or that of your audience.</p>
  
          <h3>[Ahalogy] Pinmarklet</h3><p>The Ahalogy Pinmarklet is a tool which allows you to pin through Ahalogy directly from your site. It is the best way to pin your own content with our tools. The Pinmarklet lives in your browser's toolbar. When you'd like to pin from your site click the Pinmarklet, select your image, description, and board(s). Click Schedule and you're all set.</p>
  
          <h3>Apply (verb)</h3><p>Content creators must apply to join the Content Network. The applications are then gone through by hand, and those that meet our criteria of quality, originality, and other factors are admitted.</p>
  
          <h3>benchmark</h3><p>A standard data point which is referenced when making strategic decisions and comparing results of tests.</p>
   
          <h3>Brand Partner</h3><p>Ahalogy Brand Partners are iconic brands in various industries that are looking to win on Pinterest by sharing authentic content and connecting with content creators.</p>
  
          <h3>Client</h3><p>another name used interchangeably with Brand Partner</p>
  
          <h3>co-op</h3><p>Also known as interns, these folks are vital to our success. They are students at local (usually) universities that have agreed to spend their semester dedicating their time to Ahalogy. They tend to help out the client success, content, and sales teams. Treat them well, we couldn't do it without them!</p>
  
          <h3>Content Network Pin</h3><p>A pin is marked as Network when it is from another Content Partner. This lets you know how much content from others you have queued up in your schedule.</p>
  
          <h3>Content Partner</h3><p>The content creators (bloggers) who are members of the Content Network. They license their content to us so we can use it for our Brand Partners' Pins.</p>
  
          <h3>Content strategy</h3><p>A plan of attack for a partner to win on Pinterest. This consists of different categories they can play in, what types of boards they should make, and what types of Pins and content to post. This is based on data and experience to know which tactics will be the most successful.</p>
  
          <h3>Data Science</h3><p>Analyzing (usually large) sets of data to understand Pinterest and those who use it so we can continue to improve our tools and services.</p>
  
          <h3>Data Scientists</h3><p>The lovely Data Team at Ahalogy, the people who science the data.</p> 
   
          <h3>Drink and Demo</h3><p> Ahalogy has weekly meetings on Friday afternoons that are blocked off for other team members to share what they're working on with the whole company. If you're of age, having a beer or two is encouraged. At the Drink and Demo, you're likely to see demos of the cool stuff the Product Team is working on.</p>
  
          <h3>Engineer(s) (noun)</h3><p>Also known as neck-beards. They build the awesome stuff that Ahalogy sells. We've got a handful of back-end wizards and some front-end rockstars as well. They travel in packs, and it's always best to shoot a slack message before just walking over an interrupting them.</p>
  
          <h3>Guide (noun) (help tool)</h3>
          <h3>impression</h3><p>The metric which tracks how many viewers saw the thing. Whether it be a Pin, an ad, or something else. If someone in the audience saw it, that's an impression.</p>
  
          <h3>Insights</h3><p>Ahalogy's analytics tool. We take data about our Partners' sites, content, and Pinterest accounts and turn it into visualizations that allow them to take action based upon where they see success.</p>
  
          <h3>Interstitial</h3><p>An interstitial  is how members of our network give back to one another. When coming to an Ahalogy Partner's site from Pinterest, an interstitial appears with information about the pinner, prompting a follow on Pinterest. This organic method of inciting action from readers benefits the pinner, by showing their interstitial, and the creator of the piece of content that was pinned also is rewarded with traffic.</p>
   
          <h3>KPI</h3><p>Key Performance Indicator. Pick what you'd like success to be measured by.</p>
   
        <h3>manifesto (noun)</h3><p>Everything about why we are who we are, and why we do what we do at Ahalogy.</p>
   
          <h3>monetize (verb)</h3><p>Content Partners making money through Ahalogy in some form. There have been ambassadors, we've allowed them to switch out their desktop interstitial for a brand's where they earn per impression, they've served mobile ads for our Brand Partners, they've even created custom content our brands use.</p>
   
         <h3>OKR (objective, key result)</h3><p>How Ahalogy keeps track of company progress. These are at the company level, functional level, and personal level. It gives us common goals to work against, and definitive ways to measure how we're doing.</p> 
   
          <h3>opt-in (verb)</h3>
          <h3>Optimize</h3><p>Our technology takes the guess work out of what types of Pins ensure the highest audience engagement. Winning on Pinterest requires very specific techniques&mdash;proven by millions of Pins and a team of data scientists. Ahalogy's turnkey solution allows you to not only measure your results, but automatically improves performance as you go.</p>
  
          <h3>Partner Score</h3><p>Partner Score is a 0-100 ranking that is used for all members of the Ahalogy Content Network which takes into account the performance of the partner's pins, how much content they are licensing to the Content Network, and how much content they're sharing from other Content Partners. The purpose of the Partner Score is to reward creators for being good members of the community. By sharing more of the best content from the Content Network, your Partner Score will go up. As your Partner Score goes up, your content gets promoted higher in the Content Network.</p>
  
  
          <h3>Pin (noun) (verb)</h3><p>If you're not sure what this is at this point, you should be worried.</p>
   
