          <ul>
            <li><strong>Goal:</strong> to clearly and effectively communicate new features, updates, or issues with our product. Also, to share our technical expertise and market leadership</li>
            <li>Status Page Updates</li>
              <ul>
                  <li>Use for updating the <a href="https://manage.statuspage.io/pages/3r3jz1jtb7g3">status page</a> during <strong>non-critical</strong> situations. During critical outages, let's make sure engineering is shouldered up with communications to make sure we convey the right messages at the right times.</li>
                  <li>When to update</li>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Let's <strong>not</strong> create an incident if a production release of any kind won't require downtime for our partners. No need to bother if it won't negatively impact them.</li>
                      <li>Let's create a <strong>Scheduled Maintenance</strong> post if there will be downtime during a production release or routine maintenance.</li>
                      <li>Let's create a <strong>Degraded Service</strong> incident for any components that temporarily suck. Transparency breeds trust.</li>
                      <li>Let's create a <strong>Service Outage</strong> incident if a hosting provider has issues, while we migrate to another option.</li>
                    </ul>
                  <li>What to say</li>
                    <ul>
                      <li><strong>Scheduled Maintenance:</strong> <em>Between &#91;Xpm&#93; and &#91;Ypm&#93; EST we'll be performaning some routine maintenance that will make Ahalogy more reliable but, alas, momentarily unavailable. You'll be able to sign in again as soon as the maintenance is finished. We'll do everything we can to keep it quick.</em></li>
                      <li><strong>Degraded Service:</strong> <em>&#91;Component Name&#93; is &#91;temporarily shitty attribute of said component&#93;. We're investigating the issue now and working on a fix.</em></li>
                        <ul>
                          <li>Example 1: <em>Pin score calculations for your Pinned items are temporarily behind. They'll be caught up soon. We're looking into the slowdown now and will get everything up to date as soon as possible.</em></li>
                          <li>Example 2: <em>Posting Pins is intermittenly failing for some partners, and that's causing delays from when your Pins were originally scheduled. We're investigating how to get our Pin poster back to its usual, punctual self.</em></li>
                        </ul>
                      
                      <li><strong>Service Outage:</strong><em> Ahalogy was unavailable for most partners from &#91;time x&#93; to &#91;time y&#93; due to an unplanned outage at our hosting facility.</em></li>
                    </ul>
            <li>Blog posts</li>
              <ul>
                <li>Distill down the nature of what you've done into semi-layman's terms. While our marketing and industry readers may not fully understand the technical details of exactly what or how it was done, we do want them to understand the technical challenge we were trying to solve, and how innovative and smart we were to solve it.</li>
                <li>Even for more technical writing&mdash;remember the Ahalogy voice. Always feel free to ask members of the Marketing team for help here with an early/final edit, It will help us better understand your work, and we can help you learn Ahalogy's voice and tone.</li>
